{
  "id": "L17",
  "title": "Talking About Your Work or Studies",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to talk about your job or studies at a party. Let's start by learning how to answer the most common question: 'What do you do for a living?'"
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Was machst du beruflich?",
        "meaning": "What do you do for work?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V01",
      "data": {
        "Der Programmierer": "The programmer (m.)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V02",
      "data": {
        "Die Geschichte": "History"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich bin Programmierer",
        "meaning": "I am a programmer"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich studiere Geschichte",
        "meaning": "I study history"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L17_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "beruflich",
        "phonetic": "[bəˈʁuːflɪç]",
        "tip": "The 'ch' at the end is a soft sound, made in the front of your mouth, like in 'ich'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V03",
      "data": {
        "Die Firma": "The company"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V04",
      "data": {
        "Die Universität": "The university"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich arbeite bei...",
        "meaning": "I work at..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich studiere an der...",
        "meaning": "I study at the..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Use 'bei' when talking about a company ('Firma') and 'an der' for a university ('Universität')."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich mag meine Arbeit",
        "meaning": "I like my job"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich mag mein Studium",
        "meaning": "I like my studies"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L17_S01",
      "title": "Stating Your Profession",
      "setting": "You are at a party and meet Anna. She wants to know what you do.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Answer Anna's question",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo! Sag mal, was machst du beruflich?",
          "extract_info": {
            "user_activity": "Extract the user's profession or field of study"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Mention your company or university",
          "chatbot_message": "Ah, {user_activity}! Und wo machst du das?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say you like your job or studies",
          "chatbot_message": "Super. Und magst du das?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now let's add more details, like what tasks you do and for how long you've been doing them."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V05",
      "data": {
        "Die E-Mails": "The emails"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V06",
      "data": {
        "Die Bücher": "The books"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich schreibe E-Mails",
        "meaning": "I write emails"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ich lese Bücher",
        "meaning": "I read books"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V07",
      "data": {
        "Vollzeit": "Full-time"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V08",
      "data": {
        "Teilzeit": "Part-time"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V09",
      "data": {
        "Seit zwei Jahren": "For two years"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To say how long something has been happening, use 'seit' (since/for). For example, 'seit einem Jahr' (for one year)."
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L17_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "Jahren",
        "phonetic": "[ˈjaːʁən]",
        "tip": "The German 'J' sounds like the 'Y' in 'year'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L17_S02",
      "title": "Describing Your Work",
      "setting": "The conversation with Anna continues. She asks for more details.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Describe one main task",
          "chatbot_message": "Das ist schön. Was ist eine typische Aufgabe für dich?"
        },
        {
          "title": "State your working/study hours",
          "chatbot_message": "Verstehe. Machst du das Vollzeit?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say how long you've been doing it",
          "chatbot_message": "Und seit wann machst du das schon?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent! Now it's your turn to ask the questions. Let's learn how to ask Anna about her job."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Und du?",
        "meaning": "And you?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Was machst du?",
        "meaning": "What do you do?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V10",
      "data": {
        "Die Kollegen": "The colleagues"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L17_V11",
      "data": {
        "Nett": "Nice"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hast du nette Kollegen?",
        "meaning": "Do you have nice colleagues?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To ask a yes/no question, simply put the verb first. For example, 'Hast du...?' (Do you have...?)."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Das ist toll!",
        "meaning": "That is great!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L17_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Das klingt interessant",
        "meaning": "That sounds interesting"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L17_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "Kollegen",
        "phonetic": "[kɔˈleːɡn̩]",
        "tip": "The stress is on the second syllable: Ko-LE-gen."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L17_S03",
      "title": "Asking About Their Job",
      "setting": "You've talked about yourself. Now, find out about Anna's work.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask what she does",
          "chatbot_message": "Zwei Jahre, super."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask about her colleagues",
          "chatbot_message": "Ich bin Lehrerin."
        },
        {
          "title": "Make a positive comment",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, meine Kollegen sind sehr nett."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}